stylometry: Decision theory is when you use logical compents whithin a situation to set rules/guidelines as to how you will go about making decisions. The components are: decision under certainty, decisions under conflict, and decisions under uncertainty. They are all related because they all have to do with what you know and/or how much you know. Under certainty is when you have too much data to make a decision so you need to mine the data and pull out the information that you actually need then use that to make a decision. Under conflict is when you make decisions based on the reaction to your competitors so you must be able to forsee to some degree what is coming from them. Under uncertainty is when you do not have enough data to solve your problem so you must gather more of it.
